  "response": "WWE remains popular for several reasons:\n\n1. Entertainment value\n- Wrestling is essentially live, interactive theater\n- Compelling storylines and character development\n- Dramatic performances by wrestlers\n\n2. Athletic skill\n- Despite being choreographed, wrestlers are incredibly athletic\n- High-risk stunts and complex moves require significant training and skill\n- Performers are impressive physical specimens\n\n3. Nostalgia and emotional connection\n- Many fans grew up watching wrestling\n- Strong attachment to specific wrestlers and storylines\n- Generational fan base passes interest to younger generations\n\n4. Spectacle and production\n- High-quality production values\n- Elaborate stage designs\n- Engaging music and lighting\n\n5. Consistent content\n- Regular weekly shows and pay-per-view events\n- Continuous storyline progression\n- Multiple wrestling brands and characters\n\n6. Marketing and branding\n- Strong merchandising\n- Social media presence\n- Cross-platform entertainment (movies, video games)\n\n7. Cultural phenomenon\n- Wrestlers become mainstream celebrities\n- Crossover appeal in pop culture\n- International fan base\n\nPeople understand wrestling is scripted but enjoy it similarly to other staged entertainment like movies or plays, appreciating the performance, athleticism, and storytelling.",
